# Default egress allowlist. One domain per line; matches the domain and any
# subdomain. `#` comments and blank lines ignored. up.sh unions this with
# EGRESS_ALLOW from .env and writes the result to $STATE_DIR/gateway/allowlist
# (bind-mounted here). Edit + re-run up.sh → live reload, no pod restart.

# --- GitHub (git over the :8088 cred proxy still resolves these directly) ---
github.com
codeload.github.com
objects.githubusercontent.com
release-assets.githubusercontent.com
raw.githubusercontent.com

# --- Anthropic / Claude Code (authoritative minimal set) ---
# Claude Code authenticates via OAuth (`claude /login`) and reaches Anthropic
# directly through this egress proxy: api.anthropic.com (model API + WebFetch
# preflight), claude.ai + platform.claude.com (OAuth login/refresh).
# Telemetry/sentry/auto-update are OFF via CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_NONESSENTIAL_TRAFFIC
# (deployment.yaml), so statsig/sentry aren't needed. (raw.githubusercontent.com
# is already allowed above — changelog/release feed.)
api.anthropic.com
platform.claude.com
claude.ai

# --- container registries (image pulls) ---
# Docker Hub serves manifests from registry-1.docker.io but layer blobs redirect
# to a CDN that shifts (CloudFront / Cloudflare / R2). If a pull fails with
# "Filtered" on a *.docker.com or r2 host, add it here.
docker.io
registry-1.docker.io
auth.docker.io
production.cloudfront.docker.com
production.cloudflare.docker.com
ghcr.io
pkg-containers.githubusercontent.com

# --- language / package ecosystems ---
registry.npmjs.org
pypi.org
files.pythonhosted.org
proxy.golang.org
sum.golang.org

# --- OS packages (Debian base images in build pods) ---
deb.debian.org
security.debian.org

# --- code-server extensions (Open VSX, not the MS marketplace) ---
open-vsx.org

# --- claude.ai MCP connectors (OAuth + tool calls) ---
# Remote MCP servers Claude Code connects to. Auth is OAuth: the authorize step
# happens in the user's browser (direct, not via this proxy), but the metadata
# fetch + token exchange + all tool calls egress from the pod through here, so
# the provider domains must be allowed. Apex covers mcp.*/auth.*/api.* subdomains.
linear.app
slack.com
atlassian.com

# --- docs / help ---
stackoverflow.com
